This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for the build-system and compiler boundary.

## Core concept

Build orchestration answers which semantic units to compile. The compiler answers what those units mean.

## Build-system ownership

- command and capability selection
- config bootstrap
- source ownership and graphs
- provider scheduling
- generated-function worklists
- entry and package assembly
- target planning
- outputs and incremental reuse

## Compiler ownership

- source syntax preparation
- provider-interface binding
- local declaration ordering
- AST semantics
- TIR
- HIR and validation
- borrow validation
- target-contract validation

Backends consume explicit compiled artefacts and link plans. They do not load source or reconstruct project topology.

## Rewrite focus

Explain why ownership boundaries reduce duplicated work, conflicting truth and late target failures.

Canonical details live in both architecture authorities.
